=Description=

"The [[Art of Anonymous Activism]]: Serving the Public While Surviving Public Service" is a short book published by three public interest organizations based in Washington DC. Pogo is the Project on Government Oversight, www.pogo.org; GAP is the Government Accountability Project, www.whistleblower.org., and PEER, Public Employees for Environmental Responsibility, www.peer.org. Jeff Ruch is the executive director of PEER and the book's co-editor."


